### T064: Edit Distance Tracking per Span

**PRD Reference:** Sprint 2, Task 4 (Track every edit within RED-tagged span, running edit distance)
**Depends on:** T063, T031
**Blocks:** T065
**User Stories:** US-12
**Estimated scope:** 1.5 hours

#### Description

Track edits within RED-tagged attribution spans. On each edit, recompute the running edit distance from the original paste content. Only re-score the edited span, not the entire document. Debounce re-scoring to avoid performance hits during rapid typing.

#### Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Edits within a RED/YELLOW span trigger edit distance recomputation
- [ ] Edit distance is computed between current span text and `original_paste_content`
- [ ] Re-scoring is debounced (2 seconds of inactivity after last edit in span)
- [ ] Only the modified span is re-scored, not the full document
- [ ] The `edit_distance_from_paste` attribute is updated on the span's mark

#### Files to Create/Modify

- `packages/editor/src/attribution/edit-tracker.ts` — (create) edit tracking and distance computation
- `packages/editor/src/extensions/edit-tracking-plugin.ts` — (create) TipTap plugin that watches for edits in attributed spans
- `packages/editor/src/components/Editor.tsx` — (modify) register edit tracking plugin

#### Implementation Notes

Create a ProseMirror plugin that uses `appendTransaction` to detect when edits occur within attributed spans:

```typescript
appendTransaction(transactions, oldState, newState) {
  for (const tr of transactions) {
    if (!tr.docChanged) continue;
    // Find attribution marks at changed positions
    tr.steps.forEach((step) => {
      const mapped = step.getMap();
      mapped.forEach((oldStart, oldEnd, newStart, newEnd) => {
        // Check for attribution marks in the changed range
        newState.doc.nodesBetween(newStart, newEnd, (node, pos) => {
          const mark = node.marks.find(m => m.type.name === 'attribution');
          if (mark && mark.attrs.color !== 'green') {
            scheduleRescore(pos, node, mark);
          }
        });
      });
    });
  }
  return null; // actual mark update happens after debounce
}
```

The debounce is per-span: track `{ spanStart, timeout }` map. When the debounce fires, extract the span's current text, compute normalized distance from `original_paste_content`, and dispatch a transaction to update the mark attributes.

#### Evaluation Checklist

- [ ] Unit test: edit in RED span triggers distance recomputation after debounce
- [ ] Unit test: edits outside attributed spans do not trigger recomputation
- [ ] Unit test: only the edited span is re-scored

