#### Implementation Notes

```typescript
type AttributionColor = 'red' | 'yellow' | 'green';

export function computeTransition(normalizedDistance: number, currentColor: AttributionColor): AttributionColor {
  // normalizedDistance = fraction of characters changed (0 = identical, 1 = completely different)
  if (normalizedDistance >= 0.7) return 'green';
  if (normalizedDistance >= 0.2) return 'yellow';
  return 'red';
}
```

Apply by updating the mark: remove old mark, add new mark with updated color and edit_distance_from_paste. Use `tr.removeMark(from, to, markType).addMark(from, to, markType.create(newAttrs))`.

Note: The PRD says "RED→YELLOW at 20% change" means when the user has changed 20% of the characters. `normalizedDistance >= 0.2` maps to this. At 70% changed (`normalizedDistance >= 0.7`), transition to GREEN.

