#### Implementation Notes

Compute percentages by iterating over all text nodes and their attribution marks:

```typescript
function computeAttributionSummary(doc: Node): { green: number; yellow: number; red: number } {
  let green = 0, yellow = 0, red = 0;
  doc.descendants((node) => {
    if (!node.isText) return;
    const mark = node.marks.find(m => m.type.name === 'attribution');
    const len = node.text?.length ?? 0;
    if (!mark || mark.attrs.color === 'green') green += len;
    else if (mark.attrs.color === 'yellow') yellow += len;
    else if (mark.attrs.color === 'red') red += len;
  });
  const total = green + yellow + red;
  if (total === 0) return { green: 100, yellow: 0, red: 0 };
  return {
    green: Math.round((green / total) * 100),
    yellow: Math.round((yellow / total) * 100),
    red: Math.round((red / total) * 100),
  };
}
```

The bar itself is a horizontal div with three colored segments. Use the manuscript aesthetic: rough.js-style border around the bar, Courier Prime font for the percentages.

